Process Injection via Cross-Process Memory Operations into High-Value Targets

In this threat hunting scenario, we searched for unauthorized cross-process memory operations performed by unsigned or untrusted processes targeting high-value Windows processes such as lsass.exe, svchost.exe, winlogon.exe, and explorer.exe. The hunt also focused on identifying command-line indicators associated with reflective DLL injection and other memory injection techniques commonly used to execute malicious code within trusted system processes.

Attackers use process injection to evade endpoint security controls, hide malicious code inside legitimate processes, steal credentials, establish persistence, and perform post-exploitation activities while minimizing their detection footprint. Compromising critical system processes such as lsass.exe may lead to credential theft, privilege escalation, lateral movement, and ultimately full domain compromise.

Sentinel One Query

event.type = "Cross Process"
AND (
    // High-value injection targets (lsass, explorer, svchost, notepad)
    tgt.process.name in:anycase ("lsass.exe", "explorer.exe", "svchost.exe", "notepad.exe")
    OR
    // Reflective DLL injection patterns in source process cmdline
    src.process.cmdline contains (
        "ReflectivePEInjection",
        "Invoke-ReflectiveDll",
        "reflective_dll",
        "LoadRemoteLibraryR"
    )
)
AND NOT (src.process.signedStatus = "signed")
AND NOT (
    src.process.publisher in (
        "Microsoft Corporation",
        "Microsoft Windows",
        "SentinelOne",
        "CrowdStrike, Inc.",
        "Carbon Black, Inc.",
        "Symantec Corporation",
        "Malwarebytes Inc."
    )
    OR
    src.process.name in:anycase (
        "MsMpEng.exe",
        "WerFault.exe",
        "WerFaultSecure.exe",
        "taskmgr.exe",
        "procexp.exe",
        "procexp64.exe",
        "procmon.exe",
        "procmon64.exe"
    )
)
| columns
    endpoint.name,
    src.process.name,
    src.process.image.path,
    src.process.cmdline,
    src.process.publisher,
    src.process.signedStatus,
    src.process.user,
    tgt.process.name,
    tgt.process.image.path,
    tgt.process.pid
| sort -timestamp
